I don't know why you'd go cleaver since it takes 6 autos to cleave them for 30% when you could be hitting for 35% pen from the first auto. Last whispers not always a necessirty though and his builds should vary, using the same build over and over again isn't always optimal seeing as some games incorporating a bloodthirster can help you duke it out with assassins or junglers like Yi and sometimes Youmuu's is a good buy, other times a Phantom Dancer can be better than Shivv - but if they have no MR sometimes a quick Shivv works out better, sometimes you can even just {{item:3144}} {{item:3006}} {{item:3031}}  and then go for a {{item:3046}} or {{item:3142}} or {{item:3035}} - Get exhausted though and you need to commit hard to fights and you really need your team and if they have a Warwick you're sorta in a bit of trouble because a QSS is expensive and if you didn't need to grab one you could have spent that G on early damage or attack speed and crit chance to snowball so having to buy it sets you back a lot plus it isn't always off cooldown because there are other ways you can use it - also a lot of hard CC like annies and Tahms can smash you.

Tahm kench eating your target can be gamebreaking for trynd plus he can quickly get a Q and two autos on you and eat you and spit you basically as your ult is down or completely negate your engage and turn fights into a 4v4 then spit you into his team etc or turret plus if he times it right during dives or engages where you are usually quickly focused down being eaten can get you killed.
